  "prompt": "I tried so hard to cover my dark circles, but it doesn't work at all. Why?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your attempts to cover dark circles aren't successful:\n\n1. Underlying causes\n- Lack of sleep\n- Genetics\n- Dehydration\n- Allergies\n- Age\n- Poor nutrition\n- Stress\n\n2. Incorrect concealer technique\n- Using the wrong shade\n- Applying too much or too little product\n- Not using color corrector\n- Not setting the concealer\n\n3. Makeup application tips\n- Use a color corrector (peach/orange for darker skin, yellow for lighter skin)\n- Choose a concealer slightly lighter than your skin tone\n- Apply in a triangular shape\n- Use a damp beauty sponge for blending\n- Set with translucent powder\n\n4. Skin care recommendations\n- Stay hydrated\n- Get enough sleep\n- Use eye cream with caffeine or vitamin K\n- Apply cold compresses\n- Protect skin from sun damage\n- Consider professional treatments like chemical peels\n\n5. Medical considerations\n- Persistent dark circles might indicate underlying health issues\n- Consult a dermatologist if concerned\n\nAddressing the root cause and using proper makeup techniques can help minimize the appearance of dark circles.",
